cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.OS, cs.SY, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the use of virtualization in next-generation mobile networks, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - Virtualization is often used in distributed and cluster computing environments, and the paper compares the power consumption of different virtualization approaches. 
3. cs.OS (Operating Systems) - The paper discusses the use of virtual machines and containers, which are both related to operating systems. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper studies the power consumption of virtualization environments, which is related to system performance and control. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper compares two different approaches to virtualization, which is related to software engineering practices.
